(127060, 1462, 42510, 'KageFox', 688, '', 1279257767, '[quote=''"King Of Kings"'']hi guys,\n\ni have bought a DIANA 350 MAGNUM and i am planning to put a scope on it. I have already asked this question earlier but no body replied but its fine so plz guys if you can guide me to the right choice that which one i should put on my DIANA 350 i will really apriciate it.\nKage fox if you can answer my question i will be really thankful to you or any other senior/expert member \n\nthanx and regards,\n\nright now i am in dubai so i can get most of the branded one''s but definatly i dont want it in a very high price so kindly advice which is also economic.[/quote]\n\nBro, you''ve got a great buy! The Diana 350 Magnum is one of the more powerful spring guns around.\n\nHowever, that power comes at a price; powerful spring guns are able to damage even high quality rifle scopes due to their different recoil.\n\nDr Sahib is absolutely right... you should first shoot your rifle with iron sights only... that way, you can be accustomed to it without wasting money on damaged scopes.\n\nWhen you finally go for a scope, go for a specific airgun scope, which can be found here [url=http://www.pyramydair.com/a/Accessories/Scopes/92]here[/url]. Be wary that your gun''s powerful recoil can damage some (IMHO, quite a lot of them) of these scopes.\n\nBe sure to use high quality mounts for the scope.\n\nHope that helps...', 0, 1, '110.37.27.146', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 1968, 144806),
