(130156, 3175, 98233, 'Engineeer', 2044, '', 1280301550, '[quote=Skeeter60]In the 1960s when I was a kid we used to buy .22 @Rs 6 /- per 50 rds of Winchester or Remington. The 12 Gauge were Shaheen Rs 12/- per 25 and Federal and Winchester Rs 20 per 25. The Ruppee vs Dollar was between 4.5 to rs 9 before 1970\n\nWe would roam around in the area which is Lahore DHA today; back then it was a forest of mesquite and berries and we would shoot partridges, rabbits, Jackals and porcupines and some times boar, and where we now have a fish pond it was full of ducks. Those were the days[/quote]\nvery very nice old memories ............\n1970 for one rupee 500 cal.22 air slugs. \nmy father shot 22 ducks with one #4 shaheen kartoos at gudoo barage samee nullah all head shots.\nnow no ducks land in that area............ we use to go on a scooter vespa for shooting. good old days', 0, 1, '119.153.223.175', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 4296, 148217),
