(130327, 212, 3366, 'Mangloo Ramzani', 1827, '', 1280336950, '[quote=auto_boy]\nwhy my mags are diffrent than other cf-98s .. should i change my mags ?  [b]and decocker only works when gun is loaded only... there is no way i can lock my gun without loading it[/b] . why is that ?[/quote]\n\nBrother, the de-cocking lever has two functions:\n\nOne, it DE-COCKS the hammer. Now, what we mean by this is, that it will release the hammer from the firing positions (fully back or Cocked). As it completes the De-Cocking, it would automatically have done its second function, that is acting as a Safety Lever.\n\nSo now what has happened is,  that the gun has been decocked and safety applied with one action: by pressing up on the De-cocking lever. In order to fire, press down the lever and the trigger will work in DA mode and the gun will fire (provided it had a loaded magazine in it to start with! ;) )\n\nLastly, the de-cocking mechanism will work even if the weapon is empty and no mag in it!\n\nRegards\n\n\nP.S. Hope, I''ve not confused you further.', 0, 1, '119.159.198.187', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 288, 148395),
