(131723, 3861, 131713, 'Usama', 241, '', 1280830598, '[b]Polygonal Rifling[/b] has some advantages, since it has small gap between bullet and bore which \nleads to slightly higher velocities and smooth bore accumulates less fouling and also makes it easier to clean .\nOn the other hand since there are less grooves the barrels becomes more accurate and bore surface forms \nmore consistency.\n\n\n[b]Conventional rifling[/b] is formed by cutting or exerting pressure within the barrel, unlike polygonal rifling which is formed by hammering the barrel from the outside.\n\nHeckler & Koch PSG1 / MSG90 Does have a Polygonal rifled barrel', 0, 1, '119.155.50.202', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 5452, 149942),
